CHOLERA-CONTAMINATED DESSERT - MALAYSIA (KELANTAN)
************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
[see: Cholera-contaminated dessert - S.E.Asia: recall 991220193819]
[1]
Date: Tue, 21 Dec 1999 18:36:05 +0800
From: "Hongwei" <polymath@pacific.net.sg>

Cendol is a popular dessert in Singapore, Malaysia, Brunei and Indonesia.
The main ingredients are ice, coloured syrup, boiled red beans, and strips
of green jelly. It is rather sweet.
Kelantan is a state in Malaysia. Bernama is the Malaysian national news
agency. The Straits Times does have an archive, but articles are left
online for only 1 week.
--
Tan Hong Wee
<polymath@pacific.net.sg>
